XonoticGodot Licensing
======================

XonoticGodot is a port of the Xonotic game code — originally QuakeC running on the
DarkPlaces engine — to C# on the Godot Engine.


Source code
-----------

All source code in this repository is licensed under the GNU General Public
License version 3 or any later version, at your choice. The full text is in the
file GPL-3.

This is the license of the upstream Xonotic *game* source (the qcsrc/ QuakeC), of
which this port is a derivative work: upstream licenses all of its game source
files under "GPL version 3 or any later version" (see the upstream COPYING). A
derivative of GPLv3-or-later code must itself be GPLv3-or-later, so that is the
license of this port.


DarkPlaces engine
-----------------

The original game ran on the DarkPlaces engine, which upstream licenses under "GPL
version 2 or any later version". This port does NOT include, link, or redistribute
DarkPlaces — it runs on the Godot Engine instead — so the GPL-2 license text is not
bundled here. Where individual files reimplement behavior originally found in
DarkPlaces engine code, that is noted in the file; under the "or any later version"
clause such code is distributed here under the GPLv3 along with the rest of the port.


Godot Engine
------------

This project targets the Godot Engine, which is licensed under the MIT License
(https://godotengine.org/license/). MIT is compatible with the GPL. Godot is not
vendored in this repository; builds that bundle the Godot runtime must include
Godot's copyright notice and MIT license text, as required by the MIT terms.


Assets
------

Game assets are downloaded from the upstream Xonotic repositories by
download-assets.sh and are not committed to this repository. They remain under
their original licenses as established by the Xonotic project — primarily GPLv2+
for code-adjacent assets, with various Creative Commons and other free-content
licenses for art, music, and sound. See the Xonotic project's licensing
documentation for specifics.


Contributions
-------------

By contributing code to this repository, you agree to license your changes and
additions under the GNU General Public License version 3 or any later version, and
you guarantee that you have acquired all the rights necessary to do so.
